🧠 What are Static Files?

**Static files** are files that do NOT change dynamically.

Examples:

✔ HTML files
✔ CSS files
✔ JavaScript files
✔ Images

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Why Serve Static Files?

✔ Display frontend content
✔ Load styles & scripts
✔ Serve images/assets

---

🔷 Serving Static Files in Express

Express provides built-in middleware:

```javascript id="8y3k2p"
app.use(express.static("public"));
```

---

🔷 Project Structure

```text id="m7k2p4"
project/
│
├── public/
│   ├── index.html
│   ├── style.css
│   └── script.js
│
├── server.js
└── package.json
```

---

🔷 Example

server.js

```javascript id="p2k4m8"
const express = require("express");
const app = express();

app.use(express.static("public"));

app.listen(3000, () => {
  console.log("Server running");
});
```

Open:

```text id="n8k3p1"
http://localhost:3000
```

---

🔷 Access Static Files

```text id="b3k9p6"
/style.css  
/script.js  
/image.png  
```

