🔷 What are Template Engines?

Template engines allow you to:

👉 Generate **dynamic HTML on server**

Instead of static:

```html id="q5k2m3"
<h1>Hello User</h1>
```

Dynamic:

```html id="r7k4p9"
<h1>Hello <%= name %></h1>
```

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Popular Template Engines

| Engine     | Description      |
| ---------- | ---------------- |
| EJS        | Simple & popular |
| Pug        | Clean syntax     |
| Handlebars | Logic-based      |

---

🔷 Using EJS Template Engine

---

Install EJS

```bash id="t9k2m5"
npm install ejs
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Setup EJS

```javascript id="u3k7p8"
app.set("view engine", "ejs");
```

---

🔷 Folder Structure

```text id="v2k8p6"
project/
│
├── views/
│   └── index.ejs
├── server.js
└── package.json
```

---

🔷 Example EJS File

```html id="w6k3p9"
<h1>Hello <%= name %></h1>
```

---

🔷 Render Template

```javascript id="x5k2p7"
app.get("/", (req, res) => {
  res.render("index", { name: "Saakshi" });
});
```

Output:

```text id="y7k4p1"
Hello Saakshi
```

---

🔷 Passing Data to Templates

```javascript id="z3k9p8"
app.get("/user", (req, res) => {
  res.render("index", { name: "John" });
});
```

---

🔷 Loop in EJS

```html id="a4k7p2"
<ul>
  <% users.forEach(user => { %>
    <li><%= user %></li>
  <% }) %>
</ul>
```

---

🔷 Conditional Rendering

```html id="b6k3p8"
<% if (isLoggedIn) { %>
  <h1>Welcome!</h1>
<% } else { %>
  <h1>Please login</h1>
<% } %>
```

---

🔷 Static + Template Together

```javascript id="c2k9p5"
app.use(express.static("public"));
app.set("view engine", "ejs");
```

✔ Static files → CSS, JS
✔ Templates → Dynamic HTML

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Real-World Flow

```text id="d8k3p6"
User Request
     ↓
Express Server
     ↓
Template Engine (EJS)
     ↓
HTML Response
     ↓
Browser
```

